# AI Study Hub Persistent Memory

This file stores durable project facts that must survive OpenCode session changes. Chat history is disposable; this file and `_CURRENT_SESSION.md` are not.

## Stable identity

- Course/project: FPT University SWP391, AI Study Hub team 4.
- Canonical repository: `D:\FPT\summer2026\SWP391\AI-Study-Hub-v2`.
- Primary solution: `AI_Study_Hub_v2\AI_Study_Hub_v2.sln`.
- Remote: `https://github.com/keit2901/SU26SWP10-AI-Study-Hub-team-4`.
- Product: .NET 8 Blazor/MudBlazor academic document platform with RAG chat, citations, administration, PostgreSQL/pgvector, and Supabase integrations.

## Durable context locations

- Live recovery state: `_CURRENT_SESSION.md`.
- Latest closed handoffs: `previous_session\handoff_*.md`.
- Project rules and historical engineering notes: `previous_session\`.
- Business rules and test guidance: `..\Project-Docs\BUSINESS_RULES.md` and `..\Project-Docs\COMPREHENSIVE_TEST_GUIDE.md`.

## OpenCode setup

- Global model provider: AI Box.
- Active oh-my-opencode-slim preset: `aibox`.
- Background subagents are enabled through `OPENCODE_EXPERIMENTAL_BACKGROUND_SUBAGENTS=1`.
- Agent configuration and user skills are global; they must remain available in every new session.
- Project instructions are loaded from `AGENTS.md`, this file, and `_CURRENT_SESSION.md` through `opencode.json`.

## Resume contract

When the user says `cập nhật SWP`, perform a read-only refresh: load memory/handoff, verify Git state, and report the safest next actions.

When the user says `tiếp tục SWP`, load memory and current work, choose the relevant skill, report a short Continue Summary, and continue the safest unfinished task without asking the user to repeat project context.

If saved notes conflict with Git or the filesystem, trust verified current state and record the reconciliation in `_CURRENT_SESSION.md`.

## Current workstream source

Do not hardcode a task here. The active task, progress, blockers, and next action belong in `_CURRENT_SESSION.md`. The latest dated handoff is the fallback when no live session exists.
